			<h2>Sunday, September 11, 2016</h2>


			<h3>Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Atlanta Falcons -2.5</h3>
		<P><A HREF="http://www.panageotech.com/thenfledge/linespage.html" TARGET="_BLANK">GET THE LIVE NFL BETTING LINES NOW!</A>  | <A HREF="http://www.panageotech.com/thenfledge/nfle.htm">Get the Edge!</a>
		<p> Ah yes, a real juicy matchup in the Dirty South where Tampa trots in to try to take on Atlanta. Tampa is one of those teams that some of those wise guys are expecting big things from this year. They certainly did look the part in preseason poised to take that next step. Atlanta also looks to have pretty much most of the same team that has won a number of games here in the last few years although their second-half collapse last year caused them to miss the playoffs. Still Atlanta does tend to start the season off playing remarkably well, while Tampa has been traditionally terrifically terrible in the early going. So if this year is going to be any different for Tampa, this is the spot where they can really showcase that. I have more than half a notion to take Tampa in the moneyline. However when playing against Tampa, up in Atlanta it has been fearsomely favorable for Atlanta. I don't know if I am buying 3 points favorable though, and I don't know if I agree, but our computers give Atlanta almost 63% chance to win this game here. We like that.  <br>************************************<br> <b> ATL 26 - TAM 24 </b> <br>************************************<br> <font COLOR="#009900"><!WINNER><b>  </b></font> <font COLOR="#CC0000"><!LOSER>  </font> </p>


