		<p> Now here's the kind of game we like to get some action in on. Chicago who has been the NFL's equivalent of a dumpster fire at times over the last few years look to regroup and start anew. Just at the time of the year where they also tend to play their (statistially) best. September in Chicago is they usually a hopeful time of year for them. Just before they wind up with half the team on injured reserve. Then they usually only have two problems, they can't block anyone, and they can't tackle anyone. Now before you get to harsh on me,  those are not my words, but the words of their former coach... Ditka. Mike Ditka. Ditka wouldn't stand for this, but even Ditka can't help them here, and in Houston. Taking on an improving Houston team that looks also poised to make a big move with thier newly minted expensive quarterback Brock Osweiler. If he only proves to be worth about half what they're paying him Houston should win this game handily, if he don't, well its Chicago, so they will still win. <br>************************************<br> <b> HOU 28 - CHI 13 </b> <br>************************************<br> <font COLOR="#009900"><!WINNER><b>  </b></font> <font COLOR="#CC0000"><!LOSER>  </font> </p>



