		<p> A hot one on prime time in the desert. Arizona last appeared in the NFC Championship, and deserved thier spot there as they were one of the best teams all year long. Bruce Arrians has done an amazing job there and we gave them plenty of love last year, and will be doing so again this year. New England has been in that discussion for about the last 15 years. Even in their "down years" New England wins 10 or 11 games. Starting the season without Tom Brady, ain't no big thing. They have weathered times without Tom Terrific, and still wound up alright. They have gone 0-2 out of the gate, and still gone on to win the Super Bowl. So bottom line New England will be alright. They probably won't win this game, but out in Arizona without their QB, they will still be alright. <br>************************************<br> <b> AZ 26 - NE 19 </b> <br>************************************<br> <font COLOR="#009900"><!WINNER><b>  </b></font> <font COLOR="#CC0000"><!LOSER>  </font> </p>


